Query2XML Installation
======================
Version: $Id$


Requirements
------------
- PHP5: XML_Query2XML heavily uses the new exception handling and
  object orientation features. 
- PHP5's DOM XML extension (which is complied in to PHP5 by default) 
- PEAR DB, PEAR MDB2 or ADOdb

The following packages are optional: 
- PEAR Log 
- PEAR XML_Beautifier: very handy to format the XML data returned
  by DomDocument->saveXML().
- PEAR I18N_UnicodeString: this is only required if you want to use
  XML_Query2XML's ability to map SQL identifiers to XML names in
  accordance with ISO/IEC 9075-14:2005.


Installation
------------
- Just run `pear install XML_Query2XML'.
- You might have to run `pear config-set preferred_state beta' first. 

This will create the following files:
$PHP_PEAR_INSTALL_DIR/XML/Query2XML.php
$PHP_PEAR_INSTALL_DIR/XML/Query2XML/ISO9075Mapper.php
$PHP_PEAR_TEST_DIR/XML_Query2XML/tests/Query2XML_Tests.sql
